<TEXT>&#2;<DATELINE>2014-12-31</DATELINE><TITLE>15 Respiratory medicine</TITLE><BODY>●. Upper respiratory infections are commonplace, especially in young people, and are often contagious; ●. Lower respiratory infections are often contagious and some are potentially fatal; ●. Asthma is common and may be life-threatening; ●. Chronic obstructive pulmonary disease is common and disabling; ●. Tuberculosis worldwide is an important infection, affecting people with HIV/AIDS or malnutrition particularly; ●. Lung cancer is common and usually has a poor prognosis.&#3;</BODY></TEXT>